    <td>
      <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" align="center">
        <tr>
          <td bgcolor="#000000">
            <table border="0" width="100%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="4">
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" background="images/table-header.gif" colspan="2" align="center"><b><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">T O P I C&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;R E V I E W</font></b></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top" width="100" nowrap><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><b>waldina</b></font></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top" width="100%"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/06/2003&nbsp;: 10:31:33 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> I've experienced mobs that Enrage and Rampage.  Although I understand Enrage, I've never really understood what Rampage does.<br /><br />From my understanding:<br /><br />Enrage - mob ripostes all melee damage done to it from its front arc.  Basically, if you're in front of the mob and do melee damage, instead of taking the damage, the mob does its attack damage back to you.  This can quickly eat a pet.<br /><br />The mob does not take frontal damage, instead it returns damage to the attacker equal to the mobs normal damage.<br /><br />A solo technique is to step in and tank the mob so that it turns its back on your pet.  You're a necro with terrible melee so there are few ripostes, while your pet is free from the ripostes.<br /><br />Enrage usually occurs when the mob drops below 15% health.<br /><br />Rampage - when a mob Rampages, in addition to the main tank, the mob performs an additional attack to another player on its Hate list.<br /><br />To choose this second target, the mob ignores its normal aggro list and instead seeks out the FIRST player that is on its Hate list.  This player is attacked until it is dead, the mob will even return to this player if it is rezzed. The range for a Rampage attack exceeds the normal melee range.  If the mob can no longer attack the chosen player (dead, oor, FD) it will move to the next person in order on its list.<br /><br />This mob does not attack differently or for more damage it just adds this additional victim.<br /><br />A mob can rampage at any time and multiple times during a fight.<br /><br />Rampage can be a challenge to manage since any type of Hate can get a player on the Hate list (sitting, buffing, faction, etc..).  Its best to make everyone stand perfectly still while a couple of 'Rampage tanks' pull the mob.  When the mob Rampages he will seek out the Rampage tanks.<br /><br />Flurry - The mob attacks for additional attacks per round, but there are no additional targets or changes in target.<br /><br />If anyone knows of a good description of these abilities, I'd like to know.<br /><br />If any of my descriptions are wrong, I'd also like to know.<br /><br />Thanks all<br /><br />Thanks, I updated my descriptions based on your feedback.</span></font></td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td bgcolor="#e9e9e9" background="images/table-header.gif" colspan="2" align="center"><b><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000">15&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;L A T E S T&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;R E P L I E S&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;(Newest First)</font></b></td>
              </tr>
