                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"
 nowrap><b><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2">Yenmabek</font></b></td>
                <td bgcolor="#ECECEC" valign="top"><font color="#000000" face="arial" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;06/06/2003&nbsp;: 10:37:56 AM</small><hr size="2"><span class="spnMessageText"> Ok, lotta close, none completely right =). Enrage the mob riposts all frontal attacks, when a mob enrages it does NOT take dmg from frontal attacks, and it doesnt do the dmg the attacker hits for. Say you are fighting statue, which hits for ~1000. When he enrages, anyone that swings at him from the front will be hit for 1000 per attack, it can tear through any melee very very quickly. Rampage is a strange thing, when a mob rampages, that round it hits the top two people on aggro list. So, if paladin has aggro, but a shaman just slowed him and its pissed off at shaman, next rampage it will hit paladin and shaman at same time for that round of combat. Lastly flurry, flurry isnt good. When a mob flurrys it essentially hits 7 times per round instead of 4. If you fighting AoW for example, instead of hiting 4 times for 1500, he hits 7 times.</span></font></td>
